Text.Value: Perhaps we might plan a little party to celebrate our new home?
So long as I've a roof and four walls to shelter me, I'm happy.
Not now, Morbus. There's too much to get done.
Is it really all for us?
I will help! I like to keep things clean.
We love each other, don't we?
Once the blood and guts are gone, it will be much better.
Of course, once the house is back in order.
And those like us, who suffered at the hands of the likes of Mystic Carrion. A home for the undead.
So long as they stick by our rules. Respectful, like.
Careful, brothers. We must take care of this place now.
I'm glad we're here together. It would be lonely to be here alone.
Oh, how marvellous.
He's never coming back, Lumbar. He's banished for good.
A most wonderful home we will make here.
Looks like we weren't the only thing Carrion neglected.
As am I. Our friendship is most valuable to me.
Yeah, we get on all right.
Is it time for us to play now?
Perhaps we could find others like us to move here.
Suppose Carrion does come back again - what then?
New friends? I'd like that.
I told you we would be safe, brothers. This is our home now.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Ours' as opposed to Mystic Carrion's, reassuring

Text.Value: The house is ours at last. We are finally safe.
Would my brothers even want to return here? I don't know...

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad tone - he got what he wanted (Carrion dead) but now he's alone

Text.Value: Loneliness isn't so bad. At least I'm alive.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad tone - he got what he wanted (Carrion dead) but now he's alone

Text.Value: Yes, the larder needs to be cleaned, the guts wiped from the walls...

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly stressed at the task ahead of them

Text.Value: I will help! It is good to help each other.
What a wonderful crowd we would be. Undead one and all!
Yes, oh yes! Can we, Thrumbo?
I like it here now. It's not scary anymore.
Perhaps I am the last. My brothers could not survive alone...

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad tone - he got what he wanted (Carrion dead) but now he's alone

Text.Value: If he does, Thrumbo will protect us. He always does.
Nothing wrong with that. I like a party.
So quiet here now...

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad tone - he got what he wanted (Carrion dead) but now he's alone

Synopsis:
AD conversation between the four zombie beggars when they have settled in Philgrave's Mansion after permanently defeating Mystic Carrion. 

If multiple beggars are alive, the mood is light. If 'Thrumbo alone', he is dejected.
